reviews.review_text:
Another excellent 90 Aud Another very good show at the World.  If you're a perfectionist, this isn't for you.  There are multiple flubs, including a missed chord on Box of Rain and several cases of missed vocals.  Feel Like a Stranger is a strong performance, and you can hear the crowd's excitement.  Loser is pretty solid as well, and Tennessee Jed builds to a screaming peak.  The rest of the first set is forgettable.  

The second set starts with a so-so Samson and a ripping Pocky.  The set picks up the intensity with the meat of the show, Estimated>Eyes.  Jerry nails his Estimated solo and then gets in some kind of digital clarinet effect in the jam.  They spend a good bit of time in the Estimated jam, as is typical of this period, before dropping into Eyes at a relaxed tempo.  The jams aren't terribly long here, but the second one builds up to a peak with full band jamming, and there's a nice 4+ min outro jam.  This show has a short drums and a lo-o-o-o-ng space.  If you're not into space, you might want to skip this one, but I loved it live and again on relistening.  The rest of the set consists of a bunch of good songs very well played, especially a super sweet Wheel and a gorgeous Stella with Jerry spot-on with his guitar.  A couple more top-notch performances of Throwin' Stones and Lovelight close out this excellent show.
